==========================
= PL HANDIN CLIENT (CLI) =
==========================

Dependencies:
  (-) Racket
  (-) pl.plt (Found on pl.barzilay.org)

Installation:
  First, run the following:

    raco install pkg git://github.com/belph/pl-handin-cli.git

  After installation, there should be a message about
  ensuring that a certain directory is on your PATH, so
  be sure to do so.

Example Usage:
  See `pl-handin --help' and `pl-retrieve --help' for more information.
  
  Handing in:
    # Will prompt for all information
    pl-handin <filename>.rkt
    # Can pass some information as arguments
    pl-handin --username <USER> --assignment <ASSIGNMENT> <filename>.rkt
    # Shortened arguments
    pl-handin -u <USER> -a <ASSIGNMENT> <filename>.rkt

  Retrieving:
    pl-retrieve <dest-file>.rkt
    pl-retrieve -a <ASSIGNMENT> <dest-file>.rkt

Emacs Integration:
  Coming soon!